title: Unlock a Vm in Proxmox
tags: @zettel _method proxmox
roam-id: 31b789e9-8bc5-49fb-9567-8fd2feb08c60
type: text/markdown

- login into proxmox shell by going to the web console, clicking the \"pve\" (under datacenter) and click console
- get the id of the vm and do

``` shell
qm unlock <VMID>
```
